      <span class="text-xs font-mono text-cyan font-bold">// Bottom Line</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-foreground/90 leading-relaxed mt-3 mb-0">
        Doom loops are not a capability problem. The model already knows the answer. It just gets stuck repeating before it can reach it. Antidoom <strong>recovers, not teaches</strong>. One LoRA, one epoch, a few hours, and the failure mode drops to near zero. If you run small reasoning models in production, this is a mandatory fix.
